<body>

<h1 id="h1">Want To Send A Secret Message To Someone?</h1>

<div>
<h3 id="h2">The History of Secret Messages</h3>
<p id="p1"> Secret messages have been around for hundreds of years.
Spies used them to pass important information without being caught. 
The next time you want to send a secret message use this fun idea!
</p>
</div>

<div>
<h3 id="h2">Things You Will Need</h3>
<ul>
<li>A lemon</li>
<li>A knife</li>
<li>A small cup</li>
<li>A thin paintbrush</li>
<li>A piece of white paper</li>
<li>A lamp</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div>
<h3 id="h3">Lemony Letter</h3>
<ol>
<li>In order to have enough juice, gently roll the lemon back and forth against the table with your palm</li>
<li>Have a grownup cut the lemon in half</li>
<li>Squeeze the lemon so the juice drips into the cup</li>
<li>Dip the paintbrush into the juice and write a message on the paper, when the "ink" dries, the paper will appear blank</li>
<li>Have the person who recives the message hold the paper near a lightbulb, the lemon juice will turn brown!.</li>
</ol>
</div>


</body>
